> Ha!  I have a 1999 black Toyota Corolla with 47k. 
> Living one mile from work for several years really
> helped.

Yeah, well.. well.. you just don't get to enjoy the amazing Toyota driving experience as much!  So THERE.  And ha-ha, white cars show dirt better than black.  Take that.

Yeah the 80 mile day commute isn't helping ... I *did* live 5 miles from work for a whole year and a half, but then I had to go and get another job.  Oh well.  That's why I got a Corrola, they get great gas mileage and I know I can out 200k + miles on it without any problem.  I really wanted a Prius, but with the long commute, I am not sure how economic it would be, since I'm doing 70-75mph the whole time, and I think the electric engine kicks over to gas over 50mph.. (correct me if I'm wrong?)

 
> You should get a mutt!  They're healthier--the whole
> hybrid vigor thing. 

and Michaele countered:

> There are pros and cons to both.  Mutts are not
> necessarily healthier.  It depends on the dog and
> where you get them.  

Ah-ha!  And the debate begins.. see, I hear this every day - "Get a mutt", "NO! Get a pure bred!"  
My first inclination would be towards getting a mutt at the pound, as I like the idea of saving a dog.  But, I do like the idea of having a breeder because then you know what traits the dog will have, and it won't be such a surprise.  Plus you know their health history, etc.  I've been afraid to go to a pound so far, because I know I'll go home with a dog without being really prepared.  

As with everything, more research is needed..
